layout: layouts/base.njk
title: The Model
description: The Knowledge Islands operational model — Conventions, Processes, Activities, Agents, and Tools. The five pillars that make a Knowledge Island work in practice.
---
{% from "macros/icons.njk" import kiIcon %}

<!-- Page header -->
<section class="section-ocean" style="padding: 4rem 0 3.5rem;">
  <div class="page-container">
    <p class="overline-gold">Knowledge Islands</p>
    <h1 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.15; max-width: 18ch; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">The Model</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.0625rem; color: rgb(245 239 224 / 70%); max-width: 55ch; line-height: 1.7;">
      The philosophy describes what knowledge is and why it matters. The model describes how a Knowledge Island actually works — the five operational pillars that keep it alive.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Five pillars overview -->
<section class="section-mist" style="padding: 3.5rem 0;">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div class="grid-5col" style="gap: 1px; background: var(--color-border); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden;">
      <a href="#conventions" style="padding: 1.5rem; background: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s ease;" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--color-mist)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='white'">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center;">{{ kiIcon("compass", 24) }}</p>
        <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600;">Conventions</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Shared language</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#processes" style="padding: 1.5rem; background: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s ease;" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--color-mist)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='white'">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center;">{{ kiIcon("lighthouse", 24) }}</p>
        <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600;">Processes</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Formal gates</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#activities" style="padding: 1.5rem; background: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s ease;" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--color-mist)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='white'">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center;">{{ kiIcon("tree", 24) }}</p>
        <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600;">Activities</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Ongoing work</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#agents" style="padding: 1.5rem; background: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s ease;" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--color-mist)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='white'">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center;">{{ kiIcon("route", 24) }}</p>
        <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600;">Agents</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Who acts</p>
      </a>
      <a href="#tools" style="padding: 1.5rem; background: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s ease;" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--color-mist)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='white'">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center;">{{ kiIcon("anchor", 24) }}</p>
        <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600;">Tools</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">The instruments</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Content sections -->
<section class="section-parchment section-pad">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div style="max-width: 58rem; margin-inline: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5rem;">

      <!-- Conventions -->
      <div id="conventions">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
          <span style="color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("compass", 28) }}</span>
          <div>
            <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">Conventions</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">The shared language that makes an island coherent — and interoperable with others.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <p>Conventions are what allow an island to be understood by anyone operating within it — including its own future agents. They define how knowledge is expressed, where it lives, and what belongs on the island at all.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-3col" style="gap: 1rem;">
          <div class="card-ki">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Notes</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6;">Format and type system: frontmatter, tags, note types, structural conventions for both machine and human readability. The grammar of knowledge on the island.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-ki">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Residency</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6;">What belongs on the island versus in external systems. The boundary between a Knowledge Island and the tools it uses is a convention decision — and it must be deliberate.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-ki">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Structure</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6;">Library layout: the four zones (Calendar, Pillars, Resources), routing rules for incoming knowledge, index conventions, folder naming. The map of the island.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Processes -->
      <div id="processes">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
          <span style="color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("lighthouse", 28) }}</span>
          <div>
            <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">Processes</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">The formal gates that govern how the island changes — and how it relates to the outside world.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <p>Processes are what give governance its teeth. Without them, conventions are aspirational and decisions are informal. Processes make change legible, traceable, and ratifiable.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-2col" style="gap: 1.5rem;">
          <div style="padding: 2rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
              <span style="width: 2.5rem; height: 2.5rem; background: rgb(27 58 92 / 8%); border-radius: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("lighthouse", 20) }}</span>
              <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin: 0;">Enactment Process</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">The internal change mechanism. Any update to the island's conventions, structure, or governance flows through here: draft → council review → ratification.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); font-style: italic;">How the island governs itself.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 2rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
              <span style="width: 2.5rem; height: 2.5rem; background: rgb(61 138 138 / 10%); border-radius: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-teal);">{{ kiIcon("harbour", 20) }}</span>
              <h3 style="font-size: 1.125rem; margin: 0;">Contribution Process</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">External propagation — how an island proposes additions or changes to the shared Knowledge Islands model. How individual islands contribute to the archipelago.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); font-style: italic;">How the island governs the commons.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Activities -->
      <div id="activities">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
          <span style="color: var(--color-forest);">{{ kiIcon("tree", 28) }}</span>
          <div>
            <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">Activities</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">The ongoing work that keeps an island alive — scheduled and conversational, required and optional.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <p>An island that stops running its activities stops being a Knowledge Island. It becomes an archive. Activities are the tending — the regular, deliberate work of keeping knowledge current, healthy, and trustworthy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-2col" style="gap: 1.5rem;">

          <div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-ocean); margin-bottom: 0.875rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-ocean);">Constitutional</p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
              <div style="padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Conformance</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Verifies baseline conventions and adoption decisions. Non-negotiable — the island must be able to verify it is what it claims to be.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-forest); margin-bottom: 0.875rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-forest);">Tending</p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem;">
              <div style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Audit · Health Check · Knowledge Rebuild</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Scheduled — run on a cadence</p>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Inbox Review · Asset Audit · Status Review</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Conversational — judgment-heavy</p>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Structural Audit · Wikilink Review · Convergence Check</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Deep — periodic structural review</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-teal); margin-bottom: 0.875rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-teal);">Briefings</p>
            <div style="padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
              <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Morning Briefing</p>
              <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Daily preparation: calendar review, task orientation, inbox state. Sets the agent in context for the day's work.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-sandstone); margin-bottom: 0.875rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-sandstone);">Integration</p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem;">
              <div style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Email Management</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Inbox triage with knowledge-aware routing</p>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Linear</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Project workspace aligned with island governance</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Agents -->
      <div id="agents">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
          <span style="color: var(--color-teal);">{{ kiIcon("route", 28) }}</span>
          <div>
            <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">Agents</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">The operating patterns for each kind of agent — human and artificial.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <p>The model defines operating conventions for each agent type — not just what they can do, but how they should behave, what constraints they operate under, and what authority they hold. The same island can be operated by different agents at different times, consistently.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid-3col" style="gap: 1rem;">
          <div class="card-ki">
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">Human</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6;">Full island membership. Ratification authority. Operates through editor interfaces and conversational AI. Source of meaning and values.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-ki">
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">Claude</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6;">Primary AI agent. Accesses the island via MCP. Runs activities, assists with connection and curation, participates in governance drafting. Does not ratify.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-ki">
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">ChatGPT</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.6;">Secondary AI agent. Different capability profile; complementary role. Operates under equivalent constraints to Claude — island-specific operating instructions govern both.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tools -->
      <div id="tools">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
          <span style="color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("anchor", 28) }}</span>
          <div>
            <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">Tools</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">The instruments through which agents operate — the technology layer that the model runs on.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <p>The model is portable — it doesn't require specific tools. But the reference implementation (Arcadia) runs on a defined stack, which shapes the conventions and activities described above.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem;">
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); text-align: center;">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("book", 24) }}</p>
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Obsidian</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Primary note editor; human interface to the Library</p>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); text-align: center;">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("stellar", 24) }}</p>
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Claude</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Primary AI — activities, curation, drafting</p>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); text-align: center;">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-teal);">{{ kiIcon("weave", 24) }}</p>
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">ChatGPT</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Secondary AI — complementary perspective</p>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); text-align: center;">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("grid", 24) }}</p>
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Linear</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Project management aligned with governance</p>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 1.25rem; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); text-align: center;">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; justify-content: center; color: var(--color-ocean);">{{ kiIcon("current", 24) }}</p>
            <p class="heading-display" style="font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Microsoft 365</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Communication and calendar integration</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Arcadia callout -->
      <div style="background: var(--color-navy); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2.5rem; text-align: center;">
        <p class="overline-gold">The Living Instance</p>
        <h3 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Arcadia implements every part of this model.</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: rgb(245 239 224 / 70%); max-width: 48ch; margin-inline: auto; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          From conventions and governance to activities and agent operating patterns — Arcadia is the canonical reference implementation. The model is not aspirational. It is working.
        </p>
        <a href="/philosophy/" class="btn-ghost-light">← Back to Philosophy</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
